Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Carolyn A Holman in court with attorney Danielle L. Shelton.  Irene Elizabeth Parthum appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Defendant changes plea to GUILTY. Defendant examined as to her plea, advised of her Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty. Court found that defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived her rights. Plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record. Defendant is advised she is a convicted felon and may not possess any firearms. Defendant is advised she is unable to vote in any election until civil rights are restored. Defendant further advised that if she is not a US citizen deportation is possible.  

Sentencing proceeds.  Statements made by the state, defense counsel and defendant. Additional statements made by:  Jori H.

Defendant sentenced to serve 1 YEAR at the HOUSE OF CORRECTION. Credit for 2 days time served. COURT STAYS sentence and placed defendant on PROBATION for a period of 24 MONTHS.
-
CONDITIONS OF PROBATION: 
-obtain/maintain fulltime employment/education/vocation, unless a physician's letter is submitted exempting her from same;
-no contact with victim(s), Deonna C.  and Brian H.;
-pay restitution in the amount of $4,487.12 to Deonna C and Brian H; failure to pay shall result in a civil judgment being entered;
-pay all court costs, fees, and surcharges; failure to pay shall result in a civil judgment being entered;
-provide DNA sample;
-pay MANDATORY DNA surcharge; failure to pay shall result in a civil judgment being entered.
-
-  Court ORDERS defendant to pay $50.00, per month starting 09-08-2014 with restitution having first priority, all other monetary obligations thereafter.  All unpaid balances at the end of the probationary period will convert to a civil judgment.
-  Firearms/Voting Rights/Civil Judgment Warning given.
-  No Cash Bail Posted in this matter.  

Appeal rights given. Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief received and filed. Copy given to defendant.

Defendant Carolyn A Holman in court with attorney Danielle L. Shelton,  who appears telephonically due to medical emergency .  Michael Lonski appeared for the State of Wisconsin on behalf of Irene Parthum.

Attorney Shelton informs Court and ADA Lonski, off the record, that Plea Hearing was to be held today in lieu of Final Pretrial Hearing; however, due to a medical emergency Defense Counsel unable to appear in person today.  Plea and Sentencing is scheduled for a later date in Branch 22.  Jury Trial scheduled for 08-11-2014 at 09L:00am is removed from Court's Calendar.
  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for 08-11-2014 at 08:30 am.
